His unique achievement was to win the UK’s most famous – and notorious – steeplechase, the Grand National, three times and finish runner-up twice. Victory over the frightening fences of Aintree racecourse came in 1973, 1974 and 1977, with the seconds in ’75 and ’76. Few imagined the like of this would ever be seen again and Red Rum went down in history as The Greatest. However, amazingly, the monumental hat-trick might have been equalled this coming weekend if coronavirus hadn’t seen the 2020 Grand National cancelled. Tiger Roll won in 2018 and 2019 and was a short-price to “do...